						<summary>

						<p>On the wooden beam on the ceiling of the primary school.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1683 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It states that the Southern door was made probably by Musredi during the regime of Āgākhusru Sāheb. It is dated Śaka 1605 Rudhirōdgāri, Chaitra. śu. 1, Monday corresponding to 1683 A.D., March 19.</p>						

